## Prioritized Remediation Plan

| Priority | Smell | Fix | Rationale |
|----------|-------|-----|-----------|
| 1 | Assertion-Free Test | Add assertions | False-pass risk — test proves nothing today |
| 2 | Conditional Test Logic | Split into two tests | Hidden coverage gap |
| 3 | Mystery Guest | Inline test data | Test cannot pass in CI |
| 4 | Sleepy Test | Await async properly | Flaky + slow (2s waste per run) |
| 5 | Exception Handling | Use `Assert.ThrowsException` | Quick 1-minute fix, cleaner failures |
| 6 | Eager Test | Split into focused tests | Harder to diagnose failures |
| 7 | Magic Numbers | Named constants | Readability and maintainability |
| 8 | Sensitive Equality | Assert on properties | Brittleness to formatting changes |
| 9 | Assertion Roulette | Add failure messages | Quick fix, better diagnostics |
| 10 | General Fixture | Remove `_logger` | Cleanup, 30-second fix |

Items 1–4 are the most urgent — they affect test correctness and reliability. Items 5–10 improve maintainability and readability.
